    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hi Friends üëã, Welcome To aGuideHub! ‚ù§Ô∏è Today, I‚Äôm going to show how do you check the length of a string in Golang, in golang to find string length we have to‚Ä¶","html":"<p>Hi Friends üëã,</p>\n<p>Welcome To aGuideHub! ‚ù§Ô∏è</p>\n<p>Today, I‚Äôm going to show how do you check the length of a string in Golang, in golang to find string length we have to first convert the string to a char array then we can easily get the length of an array using <code class=\"language-text\">len()</code> method.</p>\n<p>The <code class=\"language-text\">len()</code> method expects an array, it will count an array of elements and return the number of elements.</p>\n<p>Let‚Äôs start today‚Äôs tutorial <strong><em>How to find the length of a string in Golang?</em></strong></p>\n<p>Here, we are going to do</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Create a string variable</li>\n<li>Convert string to an array of char</li>\n<li>Use <code class=\"language-text\">len()</code> method to get length</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"go\"><pre class=\"language-go\"><code class=\"language-go\"><span class=\"token keyword\">package</span> main\n \n<span class=\"token keyword\">func</span> <span class=\"token function\">main</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">// create string variable</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> str <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"ab¬£\"</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token comment\">// convert string to array of char</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">// Use `len()` method to get length</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> length <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">len</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token function\">rune</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>str<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">println</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Length of the string is : \"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> length<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">println</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Output of len(str) is : \"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token function\">len</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>str<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>When you run the above program it will print the length of the array and the length of the string.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/0c90e9833eb43afeb62591492e58c442/0c20b/find-length-of-a-string-output.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 46.202531645569614%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"find,length of a string, golang\"\n        title=\"find,length of a string, golang\"\n        src=\"/static/0c90e9833eb43afeb62591492e58c442/828fb/find-length-of-a-string-output.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/0c90e9833eb43afeb62591492e58c442/ff44c/find-length-of-a-string-output.jpg 158w,\n/static/0c90e9833eb43afeb62591492e58c442/a6688/find-length-of-a-string-output.jpg 315w,\n/static/0c90e9833eb43afeb62591492e58c442/828fb/find-length-of-a-string-output.jpg 630w,\n/static/0c90e9833eb43afeb62591492e58c442/0ede0/find-length-of-a-string-output.jpg 945w,\n/static/0c90e9833eb43afeb62591492e58c442/0c20b/find-length-of-a-string-output.jpg 992w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://onecompiler.com/go/3y5cnruh5\" target=\"_BLANK\">Try it yourself</a></p>\n<p>A string contains characters as Unicode points, not bytes. len(string) returns the number of bytes in this string, but not the number of characters. Therefore we are getting an invalid count of string.</p>\n<p>All the best üëç</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"How to find the length of a string in Golang?","tags":["GoLang"],"date":"May 28, 2022","description":"Example of find the length of a string in golang with step by step tutorial - aGuideHub","social_image":"media/template/golang.jpg"}},"prev":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to give space between two columns in bootstrap?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/how-to-give-space-between-two-columns-in-bootstrap/"}},"next":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to remove the last character of a string in Golang?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/how-to-remove-the-last-character-of-a-string-in-golang/"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/how-to-find-the-length-of-a-string-in-golang/","prevSlug":"/blog/how-to-give-space-between-two-columns-in-bootstrap/","nextSlug":"/blog/how-to-remove-the-last-character-of-a-string-in-golang/"}},
